00:16:26.640 --> 00:16:30.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Since you're a biologist,
he shouldn't become one, too.

132
00:16:30.120 --> 00:16:32.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He can be a geologist.

133
00:16:33.040 --> 00:16:37.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes, but it's still
in the sciences.

134
00:16:37.800 --> 00:16:39.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Change is good!

135
00:16:39.720 --> 00:16:41.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[speaking indistinctly]

136
00:16:41.400 --> 00:16:47.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We don't want
people of his generation

137
00:16:47.360 --> 00:16:51.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to inherit a world or a country
as broken as ours.

138
00:16:58.880 --> 00:17:00.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[newscaster speaking English]
<i>There are worrying reports</i>

139
00:17:01.040 --> 00:17:04.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>that around a dozen different</i>
<i>armed groups in the region</i>

140
00:17:04.440 --> 00:17:07.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>are uniting against the Congolese army.</i>

141
00:17:08.640 --> 00:17:12.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>In a forest close to</i>
<i>Congo's border with Rwanda,</i>

142
00:17:12.320 --> 00:17:16.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>we meet members of</i>
<i>the country's newest rebel army</i>

143
00:17:16.160 --> 00:17:18.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>known as M23.</i>

144
00:17:19.200 --> 00:17:22.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The Congolese army</i>
<i>is in no mood for compromise.</i>

145
00:17:24.280 --> 00:17:29.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It is sending in thousands of</i>
<i>reinforcements to the front line.</i>

146
00:17:29.600 --> 00:17:32.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>These are dangerous times</i>
<i>in Eastern Congo.</i>

147
00:17:32.120 --> 00:17:36.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Fear has driven people</i>
<i>out of these villages and farmland.</i>

148
00:17:36.320 --> 00:17:39.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Only the weak and old have stayed on.</i>

149
00:17:40.840 --> 00:17:44.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>This isn't a war yet,</i>
<i>but it could be soon...</i>

150
00:17:44.320 --> 00:17:47.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>unless the guns</i>
<i>are replaced with diplomacy.</i>

151
00:17:48.000 --> 00:17:51.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
WELCOME TO
RUMANGABO STATION

152
00:18:05.760 --> 00:18:10.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man speaking French] The Provincial
Director of Virunga National Park.

153
00:18:12.240 --> 00:18:13.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Emmanuel de Merode]
Good morning, everyone.

154
00:18:14.640 --> 00:18:19.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was anxious to drop by the station
at morning roll-call.

155
00:18:19.080 --> 00:18:21.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Firstly, to greet you...

156
00:18:21.280 --> 00:18:27.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but also because you will all have heard
about the new troubles for the army.

157
00:18:27.760 --> 00:18:31.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We all hope it is a temporary situation

158
00:18:31.880 --> 00:18:35.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that will be sorted out.

159
00:18:36.120 --> 00:18:41.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The army will manage the situation
and activities will continue normally.

160
00:18:42.120 --> 00:18:46.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's important to hope for the best,

161
00:18:47.040 --> 00:18:49.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but also be ready for the worst.

162
00:18:54.600 --> 00:18:57.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking English] <i>I was</i>
<i>sworn in as warden by the park authorities</i>

163
00:18:57.760 --> 00:19:00.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>in Kinshasa in August 2008.</i>

164
00:19:00.520 --> 00:19:03.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
My work is to manage the park,

165
00:19:03.400 --> 00:19:05.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
to ensure that it's adequately protected.

166
00:19:05.600 --> 00:19:09.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
And that the laws of the land
are respected within its boundaries.

167
00:19:10.280 --> 00:19:15.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>But also to sustainably develop</i>
<i>the park's resources...</i>

168
00:19:15.440 --> 00:19:16.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking French]
It's far, right?

169
00:19:16.520 --> 00:19:20.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking English] <i>...to bring greater</i>
<i>prosperity to the local population,</i>

170
00:19:20.080 --> 00:19:22.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and stability to the region.</i>

171
00:21:04.400 --> 00:21:08.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking French]
I was appointed Station Chief in June 2006

172
00:21:08.280 --> 00:21:11.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
by the Kinshasa office

173
00:21:11.440 --> 00:21:16.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to assume management of
Virunga's central sector.

174
00:21:20.280 --> 00:21:24.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We are at the heart of
the Rwindi Hotel here...

175
00:21:26.120 --> 00:21:30.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it is here that
the late President Mobutu Sese Seko's

176
00:21:30.320 --> 00:21:33.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
distinguished guests stayed,

177
00:21:33.880 --> 00:21:37.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and that is where the President himself
spent the night whenever he came here.

178
00:21:38.880 --> 00:21:40.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[monkeys gibbering]

179
00:21:46.160 --> 00:21:50.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
BECAUSE OF WILD ANIMALS,
DON'T LEAVE YOUR BUNGALOW AT NIGHT!

180
00:21:51.080 --> 00:21:53.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>War has ruined everything.</i>

181
00:21:53.840 --> 00:21:56.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>When I see it destroyed like this,</i>

182
00:21:56.880 --> 00:21:59.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I am deeply unhappy.</i>

183
00:22:01.840 --> 00:22:03.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[flies buzzing]

184
00:22:10.760 --> 00:22:15.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>When we started managing this sector</i>
<i>in May 2010,</i>

185
00:22:16.120 --> 00:22:19.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>there was almost nothing</i>
<i>because there were soldiers everywhere.</i>

186
00:22:20.040 --> 00:22:26.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>However, now there are antelopes,</i>
<i>warthogs, elephants, lions,</i>

187
00:22:26.880 --> 00:22:29.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and a significant number of hippos.</i>

188
00:22:29.960 --> 00:22:32.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>So there is hope,</i>
<i>and even buffalos are coming back.</i>

189
00:22:34.600 --> 00:22:37.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>We are sure that in the next five years</i>

190
00:22:37.280 --> 00:22:41.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the animal population
will re-establish itself as before.

191
00:22:49.040 --> 00:22:50.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[all singing]

192
00:22:56.760 --> 00:22:58.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[greeting in Swahili]

193
00:23:17.200 --> 00:23:19.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Bauma] <i>Kaboko!</i>

194
00:23:30.840 --> 00:23:32.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Boko!

195
00:23:34.000 --> 00:23:35.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kaboko!

196
00:23:42.760 --> 00:23:44.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kaboko!

197
00:23:48.040 --> 00:23:49.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maisha!

198
00:23:50.680 --> 00:23:52.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[clears throat]

199
00:23:54.920 --> 00:23:57.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking French]
You know that the gorillas we have here

200
00:23:57.920 --> 00:23:59.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
at the Senkwekwe Center,

201
00:23:59.160 --> 00:24:03.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
as they grow,
they become more intelligent.

202
00:24:04.680 --> 00:24:09.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>They also gain weight</i>
<i>and become stronger and stronger.</i>

203
00:24:09.920 --> 00:24:11.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Even stronger than us.</i>

204
00:24:11.760 --> 00:24:16.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>So you need to know their psychology</i>
<i>to care for them.</i>

205
00:24:16.840 --> 00:24:19.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You cannot force them to do something

206
00:24:19.960 --> 00:24:22.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
because if they
decide to be stubborn,

207
00:24:22.960 --> 00:24:25.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you will have difficulties.

208
00:24:25.680 --> 00:24:26.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maisha!

209
00:24:35.000 --> 00:24:36.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maisha!

210
00:24:37.880 --> 00:24:39.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[de Merode chuckling]

211
00:24:39.120 --> 00:24:40.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She wants everything for herself.

212
00:24:43.000 --> 00:24:46.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Bauma] <i>That is the reason</i>
<i>we use Pringles</i>

213
00:24:47.040 --> 00:24:50.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>to deal with them.</i>

214
00:24:51.920 --> 00:24:53.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ndakasi.

215
00:24:55.320 --> 00:24:58.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When you give them
something they like,

216
00:24:58.120 --> 00:25:01.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
they realize that you're their friend.

217
00:25:08.800 --> 00:25:10.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>We do not give it to them as food...</i>

218
00:25:13.080 --> 00:25:17.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>but rather as</i>
<i>a tactic to handle them.</i>

219
00:25:17.800 --> 00:25:21.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And then,
you will always have good results.

220
00:25:37.800 --> 00:25:41.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>This is the only</i>
<i>region in the world</i>

221
00:25:41.160 --> 00:25:46.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>where you can</i>
<i>still find mountain gorillas.</i>

222
00:25:47.920 --> 00:25:53.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>There are only about 800</i>
<i>left in the whole world.</i>

223
00:25:53.240 --> 00:25:55.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Now if we lose them,</i>

224
00:25:55.400 --> 00:25:58.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>we will have lost</i>

225
00:25:58.960 --> 00:26:03.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>something very important for humanity.</i>

226
00:26:04.600 --> 00:26:08.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>It is thanks to the animals,</i>

227
00:26:08.440 --> 00:26:11.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>especially these gorillas,</i>

228
00:26:11.360 --> 00:26:14.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>that our forest</i>
<i>continues to be protected.</i>

229
00:26:15.960 --> 00:26:20.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Tourism brings in money</i>
<i>to help us sustain</i>

230
00:26:20.120 --> 00:26:25.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the conservation of nature.

231
00:26:29.080 --> 00:26:33.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>There are many projects</i>
<i>being implemented around the park</i>

232
00:26:33.600 --> 00:26:37.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>because of our gorillas.</i>

233
00:26:37.400 --> 00:26:39.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[all singing in Swahili]

234
00:26:42.640 --> 00:26:44.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Bauma speaking French]
<i>Virunga National Park is really important</i>

235
00:26:45.040 --> 00:26:47.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>because it contributes to</i>
<i>the development of our country.</i>

236
00:26:47.880 --> 00:26:49.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
VIRUNGA NATIONAL PARK
WWW.GORILLA.CD

237
00:26:54.720 --> 00:26:57.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>People are really optimistic that</i>

238
00:26:57.800 --> 00:27:01.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>the park will make things better.</i>

239
00:27:06.760 --> 00:27:11.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We always feel proud
to stay in this forest

240
00:27:11.560 --> 00:27:13.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and do this work.

241
00:27:16.440 --> 00:27:17.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[helicopter blades whirring]

242
00:27:17.520 --> 00:27:21.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[newscaster] <i>Tens of thousands of families</i>
<i>are on the move in Eastern Congo.</i>

243
00:27:21.720 --> 00:27:25.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>They're fleeing the latest manifestation</i>
<i>of an African conflict</i>

244
00:27:25.280 --> 00:27:27.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>that seems to have no end.</i>

245
00:27:28.360 --> 00:27:29.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[boy speaking Swahili]

246
00:27:29.640 --> 00:27:30.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[newscaster translating]
<i>"We heard gunfire,</i>

247
00:27:30.760 --> 00:27:32.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>so my mother told me to run," he says.</i>

248
00:27:32.880 --> 00:27:34.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>"I've been walking since morning."</i>

249
00:27:34.480 --> 00:27:40.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>The region has been in turmoil</i>
<i>ever since the 1994 Rwandan genocide.</i>

250
00:27:40.240 --> 00:27:43.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>Many of the killers fled into Congo.</i>

251
00:27:45.280 --> 00:27:48.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>The result?</i>
<i>A succession of murky conflicts</i>

252
00:27:48.440 --> 00:27:51.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>in a region famous for its mineral wealth</i>

253
00:27:51.440 --> 00:27:54.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and for its endangered mountain gorillas.</i>

254
00:28:15.240 --> 00:28:16.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[people talking indistinctly]

255
00:28:19.400 --> 00:28:21.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Melanie Gouby speaking French]
There are 60,000 people here?

256
00:28:21.280 --> 00:28:25.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man] I think there are more and more
because people keep arriving.

257
00:28:25.920 --> 00:28:28.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Gouby] Why do people keep coming?

258
00:28:28.760 --> 00:28:31.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] It's because of the M23 rebels.

259
00:28:31.760 --> 00:28:35.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gouby in English] <i>I wanted to be a war</i>
<i>correspondent since I was 15 years old.</i>

260
00:28:35.520 --> 00:28:37.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>It's always been a dream.</i>

261
00:28:37.240 --> 00:28:40.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>In French, we have this expression,</i>
"Metro, boulot, dodo."

262
00:28:40.640 --> 00:28:43.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
