00:37:47.360 --> 00:37:50.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But with the recent fighting,

398
00:37:50.720 --> 00:37:54.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
people find their
living standards are falling.

399
00:37:54.240 --> 00:37:58.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gouby] Did SOCO come to ask for your
views about what is going on?

400
00:37:58.080 --> 00:38:01.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, SOCO came in like a parachute.

401
00:38:01.360 --> 00:38:05.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We got up one morning
to see beautiful vehicles driving by.

402
00:38:05.880 --> 00:38:08.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We went to see who it was

403
00:38:08.760 --> 00:38:11.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and there were a few whites
and Captain Feruzi.

404
00:38:11.360 --> 00:38:15.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's a military intelligence agent.

405
00:38:16.360 --> 00:38:22.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We were shocked to see him doing
a presentation to the people of the lake.

406
00:38:22.240 --> 00:38:26.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He told people that,
"If you accept SOCO here...

407
00:38:26.320 --> 00:38:32.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
they will build
universities, roads and schools...

408
00:38:32.400 --> 00:38:39.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you will have access
to cultivate in the park...

409
00:38:39.160 --> 00:38:41.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
since at that moment
the park will be declassified."

410
00:38:43.000 --> 00:38:46.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All this frightens us locals.

411
00:38:46.880 --> 00:38:53.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It says, "Look, soldiers are here and
they could harm you if you don't comply."

412
00:39:46.560 --> 00:39:48.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gorillas gibbering]

413
00:39:57.280 --> 00:39:59.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ndakasi!

414
00:40:00.080 --> 00:40:01.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[speaking English] How are you?

415
00:40:06.920 --> 00:40:08.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ndeze is expressing that...

416
00:40:10.400 --> 00:40:13.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
she's not... happy because...

417
00:40:13.880 --> 00:40:17.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the breakfast is not ready yet.

418
00:40:19.880 --> 00:40:23.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ndeze, what is going wrong? What's wrong?

419
00:40:24.920 --> 00:40:27.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You are going to have your breakfast.

420
00:40:27.960 --> 00:40:29.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Never mind.

421
00:40:30.720 --> 00:40:31.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ooh.

422
00:40:33.160 --> 00:40:34.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Bauma grunts]

423
00:40:37.720 --> 00:40:43.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The daily job to do is...</i>
<i>to give them food...</i>

424
00:40:43.320 --> 00:40:46.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>to stay with them...</i>

425
00:40:46.160 --> 00:40:50.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>to play, because they don't have...</i>
<i>their parents.</i>

426
00:40:57.720 --> 00:40:58.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughing]

427
00:41:00.120 --> 00:41:02.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ndeze is smiling.

428
00:41:04.360 --> 00:41:06.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, Kaboko!

429
00:41:06.440 --> 00:41:11.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>They must not feel that</i>
<i>they are abandoned.</i>

430
00:41:12.160 --> 00:41:15.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>They must feel they are in the family.</i>

431
00:41:25.320 --> 00:41:31.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, the war in Congo
started a long time ago...

432
00:41:34.560 --> 00:41:37.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and unfortunately...

433
00:41:37.840 --> 00:41:39.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
we lost many people.

434
00:41:40.840 --> 00:41:44.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>My father died in the war.</i>

435
00:41:44.600 --> 00:41:45.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Yeah...</i>

436
00:41:45.680 --> 00:41:49.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
he died when I was very young.

437
00:41:52.280 --> 00:41:58.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>My father, he's the one who taught me...</i>
<i>how to respect animals.</i>

438
00:41:59.160 --> 00:42:00.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>So...</i>

439
00:42:01.160 --> 00:42:04.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
today, I am doing

440
00:42:04.280 --> 00:42:09.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>what my father created in my heart</i>

441
00:42:09.320 --> 00:42:12.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>when I was a little boy.</i>

442
00:42:35.160 --> 00:42:39.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Katembo speaking French]
<i>Oil is an exhaustible resource</i>

443
00:42:39.200 --> 00:42:43.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>whereas fauna and flora</i>
<i>are inexhaustible resources.</i>

444
00:42:45.880 --> 00:42:48.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Even if they are allowed to</i>
<i>exploit the oil,</i>

445
00:42:48.240 --> 00:42:49.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>it will one day come to an end.</i>

446
00:42:51.160 --> 00:42:54.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>But the park will remain</i>
<i>through the years.</i>

447
00:42:54.520 --> 00:42:57.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>From generation to generation,</i>
<i>people will see this park.</i>

448
00:43:11.320 --> 00:43:13.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[speaking indistinctly]

449
00:43:15.240 --> 00:43:17.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[Katembo speaking local] Big boss!
-[laughing]

450
00:43:19.240 --> 00:43:20.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Captain Feruzi] Josue!

451
00:43:20.600 --> 00:43:24.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Look how big he's grown.
He opened the door for you!

452
00:43:30.360 --> 00:43:33.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now they need you!

453
00:43:33.160 --> 00:43:37.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They know you are important
in that sector where you can help us.

454
00:43:37.400 --> 00:43:43.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They also know that you are
"the right hand" of the park director.

455
00:43:43.720 --> 00:43:47.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do you understand?
This means, "We're buying you."

456
00:43:47.440 --> 00:43:49.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
First accept and let us collaborate

457
00:43:50.040 --> 00:43:52.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and then they will be in the position to
give you whatever you are asking for...

458
00:43:53.520 --> 00:43:58.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
While we are working together,
and you hear things,

459
00:43:58.760 --> 00:44:01.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you'll feed us information secretly.

460
00:44:01.240 --> 00:44:04.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Katembo] Directly to you. Whenever I can.

461
00:44:04.320 --> 00:44:09.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We are trying to gauge
Emmanuel de Merode's position.

462
00:44:09.080 --> 00:44:11.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So what are we talking about?

463
00:44:11.600 --> 00:44:12.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
3,000 dollars.

464
00:44:12.720 --> 00:44:15.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
3,000? Okay.

465
00:44:15.520 --> 00:44:19.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Captain Feruzi] You'll get your share
and no one will know a thing!

466
00:44:19.640 --> 00:44:20.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[both laughing]

467
00:44:23.480 --> 00:44:28.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Katembo in French] <i>Captain Feruzi claims</i>
<i>to work for SOCO security contractors.</i>

468
00:44:28.400 --> 00:44:32.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>He is offering bribes</i>
<i>to work against the park.</i>

469
00:44:35.400 --> 00:44:39.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>This corruption threatens</i>
<i>everything we're working for.</i>

470
00:44:53.040 --> 00:44:56.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[Gouby speaking English] <i>SOCO has to work</i>
<i>with a lot of different people</i>

471
00:44:56.240 --> 00:44:57.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>to make this work.</i>

472
00:44:57.760 --> 00:45:04.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They... are in touch with
and working with a lot of... politicians,

473
00:45:04.680 --> 00:45:07.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>a few people in the government.</i>

474
00:45:07.960 --> 00:45:11.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>SOCO has an office on the lake in Goma,</i>

475
00:45:11.720 --> 00:45:14.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>but it's very difficult</i>
<i>for me to go and talk to them</i>

476
00:45:14.560 --> 00:45:18.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>because they obviously</i>
<i>wouldn't really talk to anyone,</i>

477
00:45:18.200 --> 00:45:20.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and certainly not to</i>
<i>a journalist like that.</i>

478
00:45:20.480 --> 00:45:24.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>And then I met Julien.</i>

479
00:45:25.600 --> 00:45:29.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Julien Lechenault</i>
<i>is one of SOCO's employees.</i>

480
00:45:29.720 --> 00:45:32.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's the main manager
here in Eastern Congo.

481
00:45:32.680 --> 00:45:33.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[speaking indistinctly]

482
00:45:34.000 --> 00:45:37.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Gouby] <i>He is about 30 and he's French.</i>

483
00:45:37.640 --> 00:45:40.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He started working for SOCO,
I think, two years ago.

484
00:45:40.320 --> 00:45:42.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>He's in charge of liaising</i>

485
00:45:42.320 --> 00:45:46.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
between the operation on the ground
and the top management in London.

486
00:45:46.920 --> 00:45:51.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>He told me that SOCO does everything</i>
<i>transparently and by the book</i>

487
00:45:52.040 --> 00:45:56.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and he is the one getting</i>
<i>the oil operation going in the park.</i>

488
00:45:56.320 --> 00:46:01.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I decided to start
investigating SOCO through him,

489
00:46:01.080 --> 00:46:05.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and so I started meeting him</i>
<i>and filming him undercover.</i>

490
00:46:12.760 --> 00:46:14.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[Lechenault] Right? Just sit in there.
-[Gouby laughs]

491
00:46:16.080 --> 00:46:18.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Okay, I'm going to the bathroom,
I'll meet you downstairs.

492
00:46:18.840 --> 00:46:20.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[glasses clinking]

493
00:46:47.760 --> 00:46:49.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[people speaking indistinctly]

494
00:47:05.040 --> 00:47:09.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gouby] <i>So we got a drink</i>
<i>and then we sat down for dinner...</i>

495
00:47:09.440 --> 00:47:13.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and then the conversation got onto
oil exploration through SOCO's work.

496
00:47:13.720 --> 00:47:16.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Lechenault speaking French]
It is the goal to check

497
00:47:16.640 --> 00:47:20.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
if we have oil and then we compare.

498
00:47:20.280 --> 00:47:25.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Conservation, how much is it worth?
Oil, how much is it worth?

499
00:47:25.080 --> 00:47:27.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do we start production?

500
00:47:27.160 --> 00:47:30.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But these people have their own vision
of the park's future.

501
00:47:30.960 --> 00:47:33.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They've been looking after it
for almost a century.

502
00:47:34.920 --> 00:47:40.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Moreover, it is full of rebels,
full of poachers, full of mess.

503
00:47:40.720 --> 00:47:42.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It is completely absurd.

504
00:47:50.000 --> 00:47:56.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The best solution, effective for everyone,
is to recolonize these countries.

505
00:47:56.480 --> 00:47:57.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There is no other solution.

506
00:47:57.920 --> 00:48:00.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
For things to go well,
we have to manage them

507
00:48:00.440 --> 00:48:02.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
because they are not able
to manage themselves.

508
00:48:03.040 --> 00:48:09.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They are like children, actually.
They aren't mature enough, I'd say.

509
00:48:11.280 --> 00:48:14.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gouby] You are tough
with the Congolese people.

510
00:48:14.560 --> 00:48:19.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, no, I know them too well.

511
00:48:20.120 --> 00:48:23.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking English] One of the main
problems that SOCO has had so far,

512
00:48:23.080 --> 00:48:27.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
it's the park itself.

513
00:48:27.920 --> 00:48:29.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's Emmanuel de Merode.

514
00:48:30.840 --> 00:48:33.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Lechenault speaking French]
There is this guy, who blocks,

515
00:48:33.640 --> 00:48:37.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
because he's Belgian,
from the royal family, etc.

516
00:48:37.440 --> 00:48:38.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And he's responsible for the park,

517
00:48:39.000 --> 00:48:45.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
so he's got all the power in this park.

518
00:48:45.640 --> 00:48:51.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
His management gave us permission
but he stands in our way.

519
00:48:52.320 --> 00:48:57.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There is a lot of tension
between SOCO and Emmanuel.

520
00:49:01.880 --> 00:49:07.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I think he plays
his political role a little bit,

521
00:49:07.160 --> 00:49:11.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
as a member of the royal family.

522
00:49:16.760 --> 00:49:18.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Gouby laughs]

523
00:49:20.800 --> 00:49:24.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I would quite like to be his friend,
but he doesn't want to be my friend.

524
00:49:24.480 --> 00:49:26.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Gouby] Did you try?

525
00:49:26.080 --> 00:49:29.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No. I shook his hand once.

526
00:49:29.400 --> 00:49:32.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd been in Goma three days.

527
00:49:32.880 --> 00:49:35.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I didn't know anything.

528
00:49:42.520 --> 00:49:44.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gouby in English] <i>I think,</i>
<i>over the next few months,</i>

529
00:49:44.240 --> 00:49:46.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'm going to carry on meeting with him</i>
<i>as much as possible</i>

530
00:49:46.480 --> 00:49:52.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>to follow how their activities is going</i>
<i>and try to get more information from him.</i>

531
00:49:54.120 --> 00:50:00.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'm also keen to find out if the</i>
<i>M23 rebels have any interest in the oil.</i>

532
00:50:02.360 --> 00:50:04.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[thunder rumbling]

533
00:50:28.480 --> 00:50:30.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Katembo speaking French]
<i>Okay, thanks.</i>

534
00:50:30.200 --> 00:50:33.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks, see you soon.

535
00:50:45.240 --> 00:50:49.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking Swahili]
I'll keep the car in drive position

536
00:50:49.320 --> 00:50:51.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in case we have to get out of here fast.

537
00:50:53.680 --> 00:50:54.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll go together with Josue.

538
00:50:58.040 --> 00:51:02.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[speaking Swahili]

539
00:51:04.680 --> 00:51:07.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Josue, how are you doing?

540
00:51:10.200 --> 00:51:11.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughs]

541
00:51:15.640 --> 00:51:18.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[man 1 speaking French]
This is Pieter Wright.

542
00:51:19.360 --> 00:51:20.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He is my boss.

543
00:51:20.840 --> 00:51:27.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He is a security advisor with SOCO.

544
00:51:28.320 --> 00:51:30.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Wright speaking English]
The reason I wanted to see you

545
00:51:30.400 --> 00:51:34.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
was to be able to put a name
to your face because...

546
00:51:34.080 --> 00:51:38.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
very soon, we will start
working in that area.

547
00:51:38.080 --> 00:51:40.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We will contact you regularly.

548
00:51:41.440 --> 00:51:44.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 2 speaking Swahili]
We will now give you a little something...

549
00:51:44.440 --> 00:51:46.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughing]

550
00:51:52.240 --> 00:51:54.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Wright speaking English]
Just to say thank you.

551
00:52:03.320 --> 00:52:08.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[de Merode speaking French]
It is important that we work together.

552
00:52:09.480 --> 00:52:14.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So what I want to say with regard to
the difficulties we are facing,

553
00:52:14.080 --> 00:52:20.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is that if we are strong
and we withstand the situation,

554
00:52:20.480 --> 00:52:23.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
it is because we work as a team.

555
00:52:23.400 --> 00:52:28.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Please always remember
that you have done a great job.

556
00:52:28.600 --> 00:52:30.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You have shown your courage

557
00:52:30.680 --> 00:52:34.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and some of your friends

558
00:52:34.400 --> 00:52:38.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
have died for the rebuilding of the park.

559
00:52:38.920 --> 00:52:43.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The other thing
I wanted to tell you about is

560
00:52:43.080 --> 00:52:50.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the confusion which has developed
around the oil issue with SOCO.

561
00:52:50.120 --> 00:52:53.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And what I want
to tell you is very simple.

562
00:52:53.840 --> 00:52:56.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>We are here to enforce the law.</i>

563
00:52:56.760 --> 00:52:57.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>It is law which allows</i>

564
00:52:58.040 --> 00:53:01.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>peace re-establishment</i>
<i>and country reconstruction.</i>

565
00:53:01.360 --> 00:53:06.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We are not here</i>
<i>to work for business interests,</i>

566
00:53:06.720 --> 00:53:09.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>be it with regard to oil.</i>

567
00:53:09.120 --> 00:53:11.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>It is about integrity and honesty.</i>

568
00:53:11.680 --> 00:53:15.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We have to maintain</i>
<i>the respect and discipline</i>

569
00:53:15.240 --> 00:53:17.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>which characterize us.</i>

570
00:53:53.800 --> 00:53:56.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gouby speaking English]
I'm doing a boy's band.

571
00:53:56.320 --> 00:53:58.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
M23 cover album.

572
00:54:05.800 --> 00:54:09.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking French] Okay. I'll give
the whole pack away, then. What is that?

573
00:54:32.000 --> 00:54:33.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Gouby] What do you want to drink?

574
00:54:33.800 --> 00:54:35.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A coffee?

575
00:54:35.280 --> 00:54:38.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe not Heineken again,
it's a bit early.

576
00:54:38.680 --> 00:54:40.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] It's Sunday!

577
00:54:40.640 --> 00:54:42.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You have Heineken on Sunday?

578
00:54:42.720 --> 00:54:44.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] On Sunday, on Saturday...

579
00:54:44.520 --> 00:54:49.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The other days I can't drink much
because I'm working.

580
00:54:49.240 --> 00:54:51.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gouby] And at the moment
are you working a lot?

581
00:54:51.240 --> 00:54:55.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man] Communication is so much work,
it's tiring.

582
00:54:55.480 --> 00:55:01.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am a great notable of Rutshuru.

583
00:55:02.880 --> 00:55:05.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gouby] You have a lot of land there,
don't you? How many hectares?

584
00:55:05.880 --> 00:55:07.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] 2,000 hectares, that's it.

585
00:55:07.600 --> 00:55:11.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And the friends from SOCO
have put marker stones on my land

586
00:55:11.920 --> 00:55:15.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to mark out the Block 5, their concession.

587
00:55:15.880 --> 00:55:22.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Some people don't like
SOCO doing its work here.

588
00:55:25.280 --> 00:55:32.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Minister Vunabandi asked me to calm them.

589
00:55:32.280 --> 00:55:34.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I did that job.

590
00:55:34.360 --> 00:55:36.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've communicated to the population

591
00:55:36.160 --> 00:55:39.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that it's better to work with SOCO
than work with the park.

592
00:55:39.080 --> 00:55:41.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You told them that it was better?

593
00:55:41.560 --> 00:55:44.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes, I told the people
better with SOCO than with the park.

594
00:55:46.680 --> 00:55:51.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If SOCO works with us,
in particular with me...

595
00:55:51.440 --> 00:55:54.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I am in the M23, but outside the M23
I have my private businesses.

596
00:55:54.720 --> 00:55:56.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gouby] All right,
so you would have a percentage?

597
00:55:56.560 --> 00:55:58.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] Yes, we are asking for a percentage.

598
00:55:58.920 --> 00:56:01.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They cannot exploit oil without us.

599
00:56:01.240 --> 00:56:05.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's a percentage,
whether it is 0.01 or 0.001.

600
00:56:05.400 --> 00:56:06.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Gouby] Yes, it can be a lot of money.

601
00:56:07.040 --> 00:56:09.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] A lot.

602
00:56:16.640 --> 00:56:18.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gouby speaking English]
<i>Rebels like Colonel Kazarama</i>

603
00:56:18.840 --> 00:56:22.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>are all scrambling to profit from</i>
<i>the oil exploration in the region.</i>

604
00:56:22.640 --> 00:56:24.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Although, so far, there is no evidence</i>

605
00:56:25.000 --> 00:56:28.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>that SOCO has entered into</i>
<i>financial deals with them.</i>

606
00:56:28.440 --> 00:56:34.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>By operating in this environment...</i>
<i>I think that SOCO are playing with fire...</i>

607
00:56:34.840 --> 00:56:41.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and they are playing with forces</i>
<i>that are extremely powerful and dangerous.</i>

608
00:57:06.400 --> 00:57:08.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[indistinct conversations]

609
00:57:42.120 --> 00:57:43.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[flies buzzing]

610
00:58:06.400 --> 00:58:08.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Katembo speaking French]
They used a chainsaw

611
00:58:08.560 --> 00:58:10.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to remove part of the head
and the upper jaw.

612
00:58:11.000 --> 00:58:16.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They took that, as well as the tusks.

613
00:58:16.160 --> 00:58:20.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Examining the ballistics
suggests this wasn't

614
00:58:20.880 --> 00:58:25.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the work of poachers
we are familiar with.

615
00:58:25.440 --> 00:58:28.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This was a military style operation.

616
00:58:30.600 --> 00:58:33.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[de Merode speaking English]
<i>Every single armed group that is operating</i>

617
00:58:33.640 --> 00:58:38.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>in Eastern Congo is tied to the illegal</i>
<i>exploitation of natural resources.</i>

618
00:58:38.120 --> 00:58:39.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>That's how they survive.</i>

619
00:58:39.200 --> 00:58:42.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And they all have... mixed agendas.

620
00:58:43.000 --> 00:58:48.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, they have an official agenda
that they... that they broadcast,

621
00:58:48.120 --> 00:58:50.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>but in reality...</i>

622
00:58:50.280 --> 00:58:53.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>all their efforts are focused on</i>
<i>survival and making money.</i>

623
00:58:59.800 --> 00:59:01.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking Swahili]
We will march on the capital Kinshasa!

624
00:59:01.600 --> 00:59:02.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[crowd cheers]

625
00:59:02.720 --> 00:59:05.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Long live M23!

626
00:59:05.880 --> 00:59:06.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[crowd cheers]

627
00:59:10.200 --> 00:59:14.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking French]
Ladies, gentlemen, we regretfully announce

628
00:59:14.640 --> 00:59:19.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the resumption of war
by the Kinshasa government.

629
00:59:21.280 --> 00:59:24.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gouby speaking French]
<i>So the goal isn't to gain more territory?</i>

630
00:59:24.120 --> 00:59:25.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, let me be clear.

631
00:59:25.760 --> 00:59:29.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If the government agree
to enter into dialog with us

632
00:59:29.120 --> 00:59:34.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and suspend their attacks,
we are here for peace.

633
00:59:34.800 --> 00:59:41.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If they continue to violate the truce,
then we know what we will do.

634
00:59:58.200 --> 00:59:59.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunfire in distance]

635
01:00:09.760 --> 01:00:11.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[explosions in distance]

636
01:00:16.800 --> 01:00:19.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gouby speaking French]
<i>Hey! Did you get my text?</i>

637
01:00:22.200 --> 01:00:25.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>No, no, no, you didn't tell me</i>
<i>where you were.</i>

638
01:00:27.880 --> 01:00:32.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Okay. Opposite Rouge</i>
<i>and it's called "Grill"?</i>

639
01:00:34.160 --> 01:00:39.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Okay, cool. Let's do that. Perfect.</i>

640
01:01:13.080 --> 01:01:15.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gouby speaking English] <i>I thought that</i>
<i>I would meet Julien by himself.</i>

641
01:01:15.800 --> 01:01:21.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>So when I arrived, I was quite surprised</i>
<i>to see him with two other people,</i>

642
01:01:21.320 --> 01:01:25.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>one of whom was</i>
<i>a SOCO security subcontractor.</i>

643
01:01:28.280 --> 01:01:30.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gouby speaking French]
Please be careful, sir.

644
01:01:30.680 --> 01:01:32.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gouby speaking English]
I hate that.

645
01:01:32.800 --> 01:01:34.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[John] If you pull the trigger now,
it goes off.

646
01:01:34.640 --> 01:01:35.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Gouby] I hate when they do that.

647
01:01:35.720 --> 01:01:37.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Lechenault] No security on!

648
01:01:45.360 --> 01:01:47.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] Just gonna get close like that.

649
01:01:47.560 --> 01:01:48.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Gouby] So we speak English tonight.

650
01:01:48.960 --> 01:01:50.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man]
No, <i>Français!</i>

651
01:01:50.400 --> 01:01:52.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] My <i>Français</i> is a bit shit.

652
01:01:53.440 --> 01:01:54.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Gouby chuckles]

653
01:01:55.440 --> 01:01:57.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you define yourself as?

654
01:01:57.120 --> 01:01:59.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[John] Some people would say
I'm a mercenary.

655
01:01:59.800 --> 01:02:00.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Gouby] You're a mercenary?

656
01:02:00.960 --> 01:02:03.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[John] Some people would...
some people wouldn't.

657
01:02:03.600 --> 01:02:10.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gouby] John... was this
kind of crazy British...

658
01:02:10.400 --> 01:02:14.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>former-Special Forces guy</i>

659
01:02:14.280 --> 01:02:19.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
who bragged a lot about how
he had been in all these crazy situations,

660
01:02:19.320 --> 01:02:20.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>killed lots of people,</i>

661
01:02:20.480 --> 01:02:24.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and saying these horrible things</i>
<i>about Congolese.</i>

662
01:02:26.120 --> 01:02:28.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[John] The people here are nice,
but I tell you one thing,

663
01:02:28.880 --> 01:02:31.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
